# .claudeignore — patterns Claude should avoid pulling into context.
#
# Note on enforcement: Claude Code does not have a first-class `.claudeignore`
# the way some other tools do. The harness already respects `.gitignore` for
# Glob/Grep, so build artifacts, .vs/, [Bb]in/, [Oo]bj/, etc. are filtered
# automatically. This file is a deliberate, human-readable list of paths I
# (Claude) should treat as "don't touch unless the user asks specifically" —
# either because they're enormous, generated, upstream-owned, or otherwise
# noise for the kind of work we're doing on ACE.Mods.Spellbound.
#
# When in doubt: read CLAUDE.md and TODO.md first; assume everything below is
# off-limits unless the task names it.

# === Game data (binary AC dat files; never source-readable) ===
DATS/
**/*.dat

# === Upstream SQL dumps — huge and not where our work lives ===
Database/Base/
Database/Updates/
Database/Archive/
Database/Optional/
Database/tools/
# Keep our own DB schema (when we add it) findable; don't blanket-ignore Database/.

# === Pre-existing town stage SQL bundles ===
# These are content authored by the world team. Read only when the task is
# specifically about a stage's SQL.
Content/town-stages/**/*.sql

# === Upstream core projects ===
# Per CLAUDE.md, our work goes in Source/ACE.Mods.Spellbound. Treat the rest as
# read-only reference — only open a specific file when you know the symbol
# you're looking for (e.g. for finding a Harmony patch target).
Source/ACE.DatLoader.Tests/
Source/ACE.Database.Tests/
Source/ACE.Server.Tests/
# NOTE: Source/ACE.Server/ is intentionally NOT ignored — we routinely need to
# read it to find Harmony patch targets. But avoid wholesale enumeration; use
# Grep with a specific symbol name.

# === Build / tooling artifacts not already in .gitignore ===
MODS/                      # mod build output drop directory
AppVeyor/
.github/
**/obj/
**/bin/
**/.vs/

# === Heavy upstream docs that aren't relevant to our mod work ===
changelog.md               # 250KB+ upstream changelog
LICENSE
CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md
"Git 101.md"
README.md                  # upstream readme; our README is CLAUDE.md

# === Local secrets ===
Source/ACE.Mods.Spellbound/Settings.json   # contains DB creds; do not paste contents into chat
docker.env

# === Misc ===
*.zip
*.dll
*.pdb
*.exe
